    "summary": "A transient fetch error permanently halts polling for a non-terminal run — no retry/backoff, so a single blip freezes 'live' progress.",
    "failure_scenario": "While the run is still 'running', one getRunProgress call rejects (e.g. a momentary 502/network blip). The catch sets error and returns without scheduling another tick (line 109 is only reached on success). Polling stops forever even though the run is still executing. The UI keeps showing stale progress with a yellow 'Progress update failed' warning (line 167+) and never recovers until the user closes/reopens the drawer. The comment at line 98-99 frames this as intentional ('rather than hot-looping a broken endpoint'), but for a single transient error mid-run this silently abandons the live view."
  },
  {
    "file": "frontend/src/components/runs/LiveRunProgress.tsx",
    "line": "129",
    "summary": "Optimistic cancel updates status/finished_at but leaves completed_checks/total_checks/per-check statuses stale, so the bar and check list misrepresent a cancelled run.",
    "failure_scenario": "After cancel, setProgress spreads the prior progress and only overrides status and finished_at. The Progress bar percent (line 149) is still computed from the pre-cancel completed_checks/total_checks, and the per-check List still shows checks that were 'pending' (null status) with spinners (CheckStatus, line ~195). A cancelled run thus renders with checks perpetually spinning 'pending' and a partial bar in 'exception' colour — visually contradictory (a cancelled/terminal run showing live spinners). If the cancel-overwrite race (finding 1) prevents a corrected poll from landing, this stale view persists."
  },
  {
    "file": "frontend/src/components/runs/LiveRunProgress.tsx",
    "line": "149",
    "summary": "percent uses completed_checks/total_checks which can disagree with the run lifecycle: a terminal run with skipped/errored checks may never reach 100%, leaving a 'success'-styled bar under 100%.",
    "failure_scenario": "When total_checks>0 but completed_checks < total_checks at terminal (e.g. backend marks some checks 'skip' and does not count them in completed_checks, or a 'failed' run short-circuits remaining checks), the Progress shows e.g. 50% with barStatus='success' (status==='succeeded' → 'success', line 165 + barStatus). The user sees a green/success bar stuck below 100%, implying the run is incomplete though it is terminal. Conversely the zero-guard at line 149 is correct (avoids NaN when total_checks===0), but it forces percent=0 for an empty suite while the Empty state renders — harmless but the bar still shows 0% 'normal'."
  }
]
```

**Highest-confidence finding is #1 (the cancel→poll race)** — it is a concrete, reproducible bug: the optimistic cancel state is overwritten and polling resumes because (a) `active` stays true, (b) there is no guard shared between `onCancel` and the poll loop, and (c) the backend cancel is documented as cooperative so the next poll legitimately still returns `running`. The in-code comment at lines 127-128 asserts the opposite of what actually happens. Finding #2 is the structural root cause of #1 (cleanup/`active` does not cover the cancel path and the in-flight fetch is never aborted). Finding #3 (transient-error stops live polling permanently) is also concrete and independent of the race.

